        <definition>std::uint64_t hf_time::MonotonicUs</definition>
        <argsstring>() noexcept</argsstring>
        <name>MonotonicUs</name>
        <qualifiedname>hf_time::MonotonicUs</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Microseconds since boot from a hardware-backed monotonic counter. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Guarantees: monotonically non-decreasing within the lifetime of the process (no wraparound for &gt;292 000 years on a 64-bit µs counter). Safe from any task / ISR. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
